│ expanding TripCount/BECount).\nEdit: Insert a call to ensure LCSSA for values │
│ from outer loops needed by SCEV prior to expansion. Specifically, if          │
│ PreserveLCSSA is true, invoke formLCSSARecursively on the loop being unrolled │
│ to bring all required outer loop values into LCSSA before any SCEV expansions │
│ that will use them. This guarantees any PHIs inserted dominate subsequent     │
│ instructions, preventing the dominance violation.\nConcrete patch concept     │
│ (pseudocode insertion before TripCount expansion):\nif (PreserveLCSSA && DT   │
│ && LI) {\n  // Ensure outer loop values used in trip count expansion are      │
│ already in LCSSA.\n  formLCSSARecursively(*L, *DT, *LI, SE);\n}\nThis uses    │
│ existing utility to convert required values from containing loops into proper │
│ LCSSA form before we introduce new preheader splits and SCEV                  │
│ expansions.\n\nRationale: By forming LCSSA prior to expansion, SCEVExpander   │
│ will directly reference the correct dominating PHI (%load.lcssa placed in the │
│ original exit block) and no later CFG split will move that definition below   │
│ its uses. The dominance relation will hold, removing verifier failure.\n\n5.  │
