│ I was unable to complete a working fix within the current iteration; the      │
│ dominance failure remains unresolved. The core issue is that runtime          │
│ unrolling expands SCEV expressions in the inner loop preheader using a value  │
│ (%load) defined in an enclosing loop before LCSSA places a dominating PHI for │
│ that value. Later CFG splits (SplitBlockPredecessors on the inner loop exit)  │
│ perform LCSSA preservation and introduce a PHI (%load.lcssa) in a block       │
│ (NewExit) that does not dominate the earlier SCEV expansion use in the        │
│ preheader, and the use is rewritten to that PHI, violating dominance.         │
│                                                                               │
│ A correct fix requires ensuring that either:                                  │
│ 1. The SCEV expansion uses an already-dominating LCSSA value for any          │
│ definition in an enclosing loop (forcing creation of LCSSA PHIs for           │
│ outer-loop defs before expansion even if there are not yet outside uses), or  │
│ 2. LCSSA preservation for the inner loop does not rewrite uses of values      │
│ defined outside the inner loop, or                                            │
│ 3. The newly created PHIs are inserted in a block dominating all rewritten    │
│ uses (e.g. the outer loop exit rather than the inner loop exit), or           │
│ 4. Prevent RAUW of outer-loop defs to inner-loop-exit PHIs.                   │
│                                                                               │
│ None of the attempted heuristic deferrals in LoopUnrollRuntime.cpp addressed  │
│ the root—LCSSA’s selective rewriting logic.                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ Recommended next step:                                                        │
│ Refine LCSSA formation when splitting inner loop exits so that only           │
│ instructions defined inside that loop are considered for rewriting (audit     │
│ formLCSSAForInstructionsImpl worklist construction for SplitBlockPredecessors │
│ case) or proactively create LCSSA PHIs for enclosing loop defs referenced by  │
│ SCEV prior to expansion (extend formLCSSARecursively with an option to force  │
│ PHIs for defs that will acquire outside uses).                                │
│                                                                               │
│ Please let me know if you’d like me to pursue one of these concrete           │
│ strategies (e.g. modifying LCSSA.cpp to optionally pre-create PHIs, or        │
│ filtering RAUW in SplitBlockPredecessors) and I can implement that targeted   │
│ patch.                                                                        │
